description: A Rajasthan court acquitted the last eight of the accused in the 1987 Roop Kanwar 'sati glorification' case due to inadequate evidence, ending a 36-year-long trial. The case revolved around the forced immolation of 18-year-old widow Roop Kanwar. The incident led to the enactment of the Commission of Sati (Prevention) Act in 1987.
title: Court acquits last 8 accused in '87 'sati' glorification case

description: Karnataka HC acquitted three convicts, including a Pakistani national, in a 2012 terror case due to insufficient evidence. The court noted lapses in referring the UAPA case to an independent authority. Rehman’s conviction under the Arms Act and Explosive Substances Act was upheld.
title: ‘Inadequate proof’: 3 serving life terms under UAPA in terror case acquitted

description: Six of seven independent MLAs in J&K are likely to support NC, enabling the party to form a government without Congress or CPM. NC, with 42 seats, would reach a majority with independents' backing. Omar Abdullah acknowledges PM Modi's message and anticipates NC's Supreme Court challenge against MLA nominations.
title: 6 Independent MLAs may back NC, taking it to magic no. of 48

description: A Dehradun Pocso court sentenced an 18-year-old footballer to three years' rigorous imprisonment for kidnapping a 17-year-old girl he met during training. Despite the girl's non-support for the prosecution, the court convicted him while acquitting him of rape charges.
title: 3 years' RI for footballer, then 18, for eloping with minor in 2022

description: Leader of opposition Rahul Gandhi addressed the unexpected Haryana poll results, promising continued advocacy for justice and voter voices. He expressed gratitude to Haryana's people and party workers, and a Congress delegation submitted complaints to the EC. Additionally, Gandhi celebrated the NC-Congress alliance's win in J&K as a constitutional victory.
title: Haryana result 'unexpected', Congress analysing it: Rahul Gandhi

description: More than 10 tigers have vanished from Pilibhit's Amaria block, raising concerns among forest officials. Leopards now occupy the sugarcane fields that were once tiger habitats. Pilibhit Tiger Reserve's divisional forest officer has called for a high-level investigation to determine whether poaching or migration is responsible, and proposed relocating some tigers to other sanctuaries.
title: Poaching fears: Probe sought as 10 'sugarcane tigers' missing

description: The Indian government has approved the construction of two nuclear-powered attack submarines and the acquisition of 31 weaponised MQ-9B Predator drones from the US, with a combined cost of approximately Rs 68,000 crore, to strengthen military capabilities against China's regional assertiveness.
title: Govt clears project to build 2 N-subs, deal to buy 31 Predator drones

description: PM Narendra Modi criticized Congress for exploiting caste issues among Hindus to cause divisions while ignoring caste distinctions within the Muslim community. He accused the opposition of fostering fear among Muslims for electoral gain and emphasized Congress's approach as a betrayal of national unity.
title: Congress bent on dividing Hindu society on caste lines: PM Modi

description: Ratan Tata, post-retirement, invested in over 50 startups including Snapdeal, Ola, and Paytm, using personal investment vehicle RNT Associates and UC-RNT, aiding their growth with his significant insights. Many startups benefitted from his mentorship, with some going public and delivering multi-bagger returns.
title: Startups looked up to him as mentor, not just as investor

description: Ratan Tata strategically used retirement policies to consolidate power and modernize Tata Group starting in 1992. He mandated directors retire at 75, forcing several senior leaders out. The policy evolved over the years, reflecting his evolving strategy and maintaining his influence.
title: How Tata unseated old guard to gain control, reshape the group

description: INDIA bloc allies have criticized Congress for neglecting coalition partners and exhibiting overconfidence after its poor performance in Haryana and J&K elections. They urged Congress to be more accommodating and shed its sense of entitlement ahead of upcoming state elections and byelections.
title: 'Arrogant': Day after Congress poll debacle, allies twist the knife

description: The Tata Nano, conceptualized by Ratan Tata to offer an affordable car for middle-class Indians, faced numerous challenges. Despite initial popularity, issues from factory location controversies, safety concerns, and its branding as a 'poor man's car' led to its decline and eventual discontinuation by 2019.
title: Ratan Tata's most audacious project: Nano's 'cheap' tag proved costly

description: Ratan Tata's leadership during India's economic liberalisation transformed Tata Group through strategic divestments, global partnerships, and key acquisitions like Jaguar-Land Rover. He improved corporate governance, solidified control, and took TCS public, raising $1.2 billion. Despite crises, including a financial scandal and terrorist attack, Tata’s legacy endures, leaving a monumental impact on Indian business.
title: Visionary who led Tatas' revenue from $4bn to $100bn

description: Ratan Tata, chairman emeritus of Tata Sons, has passed away at Mumbai's Breach Candy Hospital. Noel Tata, his half-brother, is a likely successor. Noel Tata has a strong background within the Tata Group, holding various significant positions, including chairmanships and trusteeships.
title: Ratan Tata passes away: Meet Noel Tata, speculated to be his likely successor

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai and other leaders mourn the passing of Ratan Tata, the 86-year-old former chairman of Tata Sons whose business and philanthropic contributions shaped India's economy. Tata's legacy of ethical leadership is deeply honored by peers like Mukesh Ambani, Anand Mahindra, and Harsh Goenka.
title: Google CEO Sundar Pichai remembers his last meeting with Ratan Tata

description: Ratan Naval Tata passed away at 86. He led the Tata Group's transformation into a global giant, significantly boosting revenue and diversifying its portfolio. Known for innovation and philanthropy, his tenure saw projects like Nano and acquisitions expanding Tata's reach. Post-retirement, he remained active in startups and charity.
title: India loses a Ratan: The visionary who took India Inc global passes away at 86

description: Veteran industrialist Ratan Tata, known for transforming Tata Group into a global conglomerate through strategic acquisitions and business expansions, passed away at 86. His tenure saw the growth and modernization of the group, maintaining its traditional values. He was also a noted philanthropist and received several prestigious awards.
title: Ratan Tata: The industry titan with a golden heart
A legacy to remember: Top 20 quotes by Ratan Tata

description: In 1991, Ratan Tata took over as the chairman of the Tata Group from his uncle, JRD, who had been in charge for more than half a century. Ratan Naval Tata, a titan of industry, passed away at the age of 86.
title: Ratan Tata: Life, career milestones & timeline of India’s industry giant

description: Ratan Tata, former chairman of Tata Group who led its global expansion and numerous landmark acquisitions, passed away at 86. Under his leadership, the group acquired international firms like Tetley, Corus, and Jaguar-Land Rover. His legacy includes major contributions to the automotive industry with the Indica and Nano models.
title: How Ratan Tata put the Tata Group on global map

description: India boosted their Women's T20 World Cup semi-final hopes with an 82-run win over Sri Lanka, driven by half-centuries from Harmanpreet Kaur and Smriti Mandhana. India set a high score of 172-3, while Sri Lanka fell for 90, eliminating their semi-final chances. India’s bowlers Arundhati Reddy and Asha Sobhana took three wickets each.
title: Harmanpreet stars as India beat SL to boost semis chances

description: India revived their Women's T20 World Cup campaign by defeating Sri Lanka with a 82-run victory, boosting their semifinal chances. Now second in Group A, India must beat Australia and maintain a superior net run rate to advance, depending on other match outcomes.
title: Explained: What India's big win over SL means for their semifinals chances

description: Ratan Tata, the revered emeritus chairman of Tata Group and Tata Sons, passed away at 86. He significantly influenced the Tata Group, leading key initiatives such as Tata Teleservices and Tata Consultancy Services’ IPO. Post-retirement, he remained an influential figure, overseeing Tata Trusts and supporting over 30 start-ups. Tata's legacy in business and philanthropy continues to inspire.
title: Ratan Tata, Padma Vibhushan industrialist , dies at 86

description: Pakistani border troops clashed with Afghan Taliban fighters after an attack on a border post, resulting in significant Taliban casualties. The incident, part of ongoing tensions, happened during fence repair work along the Naushki-Ghazni sector. Recent unprovoked aggression from the Afghan side has strained the hopes of improved relations following the Taliban’s rise to power in 2021.
title: Pakistan, Afghan fight it out at border amid fencing work

description: A district court in Kasganj has sentenced Mahipal Singh to life imprisonment for murdering his five-year-old daughter, Somvati, in 2018. Seeing her as a burden, Singh forced her into a sack and set her ablaze. The court also imposed a fine of Rs 50,000.
title: Man puts 5-year-old daughter in sack & sets her ablaze, gets life term

description: India's Radha Yadav stunned the crowd in the Women's T20 World Cup Group A game in Dubai with a spectacular catch to dismiss Sri Lanka's Vishmi Gunaratne for a duck. Earlier, opener Smriti Mandhana and skipper Harmanpreet Kaur's impressive half-centuries led India to a formidable total of 172 for three.
title: Watch: Radha takes a stunner to send back Vishmi for a duck

description: The Indian Council of Medical Research-National Institute of Virology has developed a rapid monkeypox test kit using LAMP technology. Set to be commercially available within a month, the kit promises 100% sensitivity and specificity, delivering results in just an hour at a cost between Rs 350 and Rs 400, significantly reducing testing costs and time.
title: India’s first rapid Mpox test kit to hit markets soon: ICMR-NIV

description: Nitish Kumar Reddy's explosive 74, supported by Rinku Singh's fierce 53, led India to a dominating 86-run victory over Bangladesh in the second T20I. India's bowlers restricted Bangladesh to 135 for 9, securing an unassailable 2-0 series lead with exceptional all-round performance.
title: 2nd T20I: India claim series with big win over B'desh

description: Kamala Harris embarked on a media blitz, appearing on several shows to humanize her image and connect with voters. She received a warm reception despite criticism from Trump supporters. Highlights include sharing personal stories and interests, such as caring for her mother and being a fan of Formula One racing.
title: Kamala gets warm reception in softball interviews, hardball reaction from MAGA

description: Reliance Retail has re-entered the quick commerce market in select areas through JioMart, competing with Blinkit, Swiggy Instamart, and BigBasket. The company will use its existing store network and the logistics service Grab to offer zero delivery fees and target smaller cities and towns.
title: Reliance Retail starts testing its Swiggy, Blinkit rival

description: Meteorologist John Morales choked up while reporting the impending impact of Hurricane Milton on Tampa Bay, already classified as a severe Category 5 storm. Florida governor DeSantis and VP Kamala Harris are embroiled in political tussles over relief efforts, while climate change remains largely unaddressed amidst the crisis.
title: Hurricane Milton roars toward US retirees paradise amid political storm
Congress's 'alliance of convenience' comes under fire after Haryana debacle

description: A Turkish Airlines pilot collapsed and died mid-flight on an Airbus 350 from Seattle to Istanbul, prompting an emergency landing in New York. Despite first aid efforts by the crew, the 59-year-old pilot, who had no prior health issues as per a recent medical exam, passed away before the plane landed.
title: Turkish Airlines pilot dies mid-flight prompting emergency landing in New York

description: On October 8th, 2024, Italian Minister Matteo Piantedosi ordered the deportation of Bologna-based imam Zulfiqar Khan, citing his growing radicalism, anti-Western and antisemitic rhetoric, and support for Hamas. Khan had been in Italy since 1995, but his residence permit was revoked. Authorities linked him to Islamist extremists and accused him of promoting hate speech, homophobia, and violence against non-Muslims. The move signalled Italy’s firm stance against terrorism and extremism, especially following the October 7th massacre. Khan's deportation coincided with US sanctions on another Italy-based imam, Mohammad Hannoun, for his Hamas ties.
title: Meloni's Italy expels pro-Hamas Imam Zulfiqar Khan

description: "Stone Cold" Steve Austin's comments on the Netflix docuseries "Mr. McMahon" have incited debate within the wrestling community after he dismissed the belief in CTE. Fellow WWE Hall of Famer Rikishi reflects on the past era's pressures to ignore injuries and keep performing, highlighting the stark contrast with today's heightened awareness of head injuries.
title: WWE Hall of Famer responds to Steve Austin's views on CTE from McMahon Netflix docuseries

description: Bollywood actor Sanjay Dutt, popularly known as Munna bhai, has married his third wife Manyata Dutt for the fourth time. The couple renewed their vows during a puja ceremony at their renovated home. Sanjay Dutt was last seen in the movie ‘Ghudchadi,’ available on Jiocinema.
title: Sanjay Dutt getting married again, for fourth time? Here's what we know

description: Sanju Samson's inconsistent performance remains a contentious issue, with fans and critics vocalizing their concerns after his recent failures against Bangladesh. Former opener Aakash Chopra stressed the importance of consistency for Samson to cement his spot in the Indian T20I team.
title: 'Main kasam khata hu...': Samson draws fans ire after another failure

description: The US government is considering legal action to compel Google to divest assets like Chrome and Android, accusing it of maintaining an illegal monopoly in search. Proposals could bar Google from pre-installation payments and ensure competitors' access to data, potentially reshaping online information access.
title: US hints at breakup of Google search dominance in landmark case

description: The Congress party submitted complaints to the Election Commission of India regarding alleged discrepancies in 20 assembly constituencies during Haryana elections. Bhupinder Hooda and Pawan Khera cited irregularities in vote counting and machine functionality as reasons for their concerns, seeking a thorough investigation. Congress leader Pawan Khera said that the Election Commission officials' reaction was "as usual a good smile and a good cup of tea but we need more".
title: 'Usual good smile, but ... ': Congress on what happened inside EC office

description: During an appearance on the Flagrant Podcast, Donald Trump spoke highly of Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi, calling him a "friend" and praising his leadership as stabilising India. Trump described Modi as a "killer" in political dealings despite his calm exterior. Reflecting on the 2019 Howdy Modi event in Houston, Trump recalled the large turnout and their shared resolve during crises. He also noted that when India was threatened, Modi would adopt a determined stance, assuring Trump that he would "do anything necessary" to defend the country.
title: ‘Anyone threatens India, he’s a total killer’: Trump on PM Modi

description: King Salman of Saudi Arabia, 88, has recuperated from a recent lung infection after undergoing medical tests. Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, who oversees daily governance, conveyed gratitude for public concern. King Salman’s health is a significant matter due to his role since 2015 and the nation's ongoing economic reforms.
title: Saudi King Salman recuperates after medical exams for lung inflammation

description: During the Natwest Series in 2002, former Indian cricketer Virender Sehwag was punched by his coach John Wright for playing lofted shots while underperforming. Ganguly recounted the tense dressing room atmosphere and assured Sehwag on the bus. Sehwag’s casual acceptance of the incident highlighted the unique dynamics within the team.
title: When Team India coach punched Virender Sehwag

description: Asaduddin Owaisi criticizes Omar Abdullah's potential leadership as the weakest CM if elected in J&K, questioning the role of the CM under current nomination rules. He opposes the abolition of Article 370, while Omar Abdullah calls for the restoration of statehood as a promise to be fulfilled.
title: Owaisi thinks Omar Abdullah will be the weakest CM, here's why

description: Kolkata police halted junior doctors' 'Abhaya Parikrama' rally intended to raise awareness about their demands during Durga Puja. The protests follow the rape-murder of a medic and include demands for justice, administrative accountability, and systemic improvements in healthcare services.
title: Kolkata police halts 'Abhaya Parikrama' rally at Durga puja pandals

description: The chief minister's office has accused Delhi lieutenant governor V K Saxena of removing Atishi's belongings from the official residence, allegedly to allocate it to a BJP leader. Delhi BJP President Virendraa Sachdeva criticized Arvind Kejriwal's handling of his former residence and questioned the need for the move.
title: Delhi CM office says Atishi's belongings removed from residence on LG's order

description: Geoffrey Hinton, often dubbed the 'Godfather of AI,' received the 2024 Nobel Prize in Physics for groundbreaking work in machine learning and neural networks. His middle name, Everest, honors his great-great-granduncle, Sir George Everest, linking Hinton’s innovations to his family's legacy of exploration and excellence.
title: Nobel Laureate Geoffrey Hinton’s Everest-sized connection to India

description: A video shared by the BCCI shows India captain Suryakumar Yadav humorously teasing bowling coach Morne Morkel in Hindi before the second ODI against Bangladesh. Morkel, a former South African player, joined India's coaching staff, replacing Paras Mhambrey. The playful moment highlighted their camaraderie, with Morkel humorously asking the footage to be edited out.
title: 'Kya hua, bolo?': Surya pulls Morkel's leg in hilarious exchange

description: Ratan Tata, chairman emeritus of Tata Sons, one of India's largest conglomerates, is in critical condition in intensive care at a Mumbai hospital. At 86, Tata has reported undergoing routine medical checks due to age-related conditions, while assuring the public that he's in good spirits.
title: Ratan Tata in hospital intensive care, sources say

description: YSRCP chief YS Jagan Mohan Reddy supports Congress's claims of EVM rigging, advocating for a return to paper ballots to ensure election transparency. Referring to the unexpected Haryana assembly election results, Reddy draws parallels with Andhra Pradesh, calling for confidence in democratic processes by adopting the paper ballot used in developed countries. Senior Congress leader Jairam Ramesh said the Congress has been made to lose but it "has not lost".
title: 'It's time we ...': Jagan Reddy backs Congress's EVM 'manipulation' claim

description: A product designer quit his job on the first day due to a manager's expectation of unpaid overtime and dismissal of work-life balance as 'western developed nation behavior.' His resignation highlights concerns over toxic work culture and the importance of employee well-being.
title: Man quits on Day 1 after manager calls work-life balance 'Western Behaviour'

description: A US district court has ruled that Cognizant engaged in discriminatory practices against non-Indian employees. Former workers claimed they faced bias from Indian managers, who excluded them from discussions and promotions. The plaintiffs also accused Cognizant of fraudulent visa practices. Cognizant plans to appeal the decision.
title: What discrimination lawsuit filed by Cognizant’s ex-employees claims

description: Centre extends free fortified rice under welfare programs like PMGKAY until 2028 to combat anaemia and micronutrient deficiencies, costing Rs 17,082 crore. Fortified rice, enriched with Iron, Folic Acid, and Vitamin B12, is now in all government schemes. Additionally, approvals were given for road construction in border areas and a National Maritime Heritage Complex in Gujarat.
title: Union Cabinet meet: What are the three key decisions announced by govt

description: Sheryl Sandberg, former COO of Meta, has begun a campaign to highlight the brutality of Hamas's attack on Israel in October 2023 through her film, Screams Before Silence.
title: Former Facebook COO makes movie on Hamas attack on Israel for students

description: Hurricane Milton embodies the type of storm climate experts have long cautioned about. Michael Wehner, a climate scientist at Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, remarked that while the storm's intensity is shocking, it is not unexpected. The warmer climate has given rise to storms that, while still formidable in their own right, are now exacerbated by environmental changes.Milton’s development was driven by multiple factors that combined to create a catastrophic storm.
title: Explained: Why scientists consider Hurricane Milton most dangerous storm

description: Former US President Trump secretly sent Covid-19 testing devices to Russian President Putin during the pandemic, while devices were scarce. The Kremlin confirmed the shipment but denied phone conversations post-Trump presidency. This revelation has sparked criticism from US VP Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden, who accuse Trump of compromising national security by being too close to dictators.
title: Kremlin: Trump sent Putin Covid tests while President

description: During the first Test against Pakistan, England's Harry Brook narrowly avoided dismissal when a ball hit his stumps but left the bails unmoved. Joe Root dazzled with a record-breaking 119 not out, surpassing Alastair Cook as England's top Test run-scorer. Brook's near-miss aside, he scored a solid 64, contributing to England's strong position at 351/3.
title: Watch: Ball hits wicket but bails remain intact, Brook survives

description: Hinton's concerns are rooted in his long-standing commitment to the ethical development of AI. In 2009, Hinton demonstrated the potential of Nvidia’s CUDA platform by training a neural network to recognise human speech, an achievement that contributed to the wider use of GPUs in AI research.
title: Why 'Godfather of AI' and Nobel Laureate Hinton hates Sam Altman and OpenAI

description: Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge accused the Election Commission of EVM tampering in Haryana elections. Congress labeled the results 'unacceptable' and suggested irregularities linked to battery charges. The EC refuted these claims as undemocratic, calling for a meeting with the party to address grievances.
title: 'Unprecedented statement': EC's sharp reply to Kharge on Congress' Haryana results 'unacceptable' remark

description: An Apple Watch helped save an elderly woman by detecting her atrial fibrillation. The notification prompted her to seek medical attention, which prevented further complications. Many users shared similar experiences, praising the health monitoring capabilities of the device. The Apple Watch continues to play a vital role in personal healthcare with its advanced features.
title: How the Apple Watch Series 10 saved an elderly woman's life

description: Magnesium could help you sleep better by promoting relaxation and reducing stress. It influences neurotransmitters, relaxes muscles, boosts melatonin, and lowers stress hormones. Including magnesium-rich foods like leafy greens, beans, and nuts in your diet can be beneficial. Consult a healthcare provider before taking supplements to avoid potential risks.
title: Magnesium for better sleep: Can this mineral really help you sleep deeper and longer?

description: Healthcare services in West Bengal remained operational despite mass resignations from senior doctors at various medical colleges. The resignations aim to pressure the state government into addressing the demands of protesting junior doctors. Despite Durga Puja, hospitals ensured minimal disruption by managing duty rosters and backup staff effectively.
title: RG Kar protest: West Bengal doctors say mass resignation 'symbolic'

description: A 65-year-old woman from south Mumbai was defrauded of Rs 1.3 crore in a complex scam involving emotional manipulation and fake officials over a year, initially starting through a dating app. The scam progressed with fake calls from various financial institutions and officials demanding payments for fictitious services.
title: How a woman was scammed of Rs 1.3 cr on dating app through calls & letters

description: Prime Minister Modi accused Congress of creating 'fear psychosis' among Muslims to secure votes, while highlighting BJP's re-election success in Haryana and criticising Congress's tactics towards Dalits, farmers, and youth. Modi urged disunity opposition in Maharashtra to counter Congress's divisive measures.
title: 'Congress creating fear psychosis in minds of Muslims': PM Modi

description: The Samajwadi Party has released candidates for six Uttar Pradesh bypolls without consulting the INDIA bloc, sparking discontent within the alliance. Key nominations include Tej Pratap Yadav for Karhal and Ajit Prasad for Milkipur. The development follows Congress's underperformance in Haryana, raising concerns about alliance coordination ahead of the 2024 Lok Sabha polls.
title: UP bypolls: Congress claims SP didn't discuss candidates with INDIA bloc

description: David Baker wins half of the 2024 Nobel Prize in Chemistry for computational protein design, while Demis Hassabis and John M. Jumper share the other half for protein structure prediction. The Nobel Prize announcements kicked off with Victor Ambros and Gary Ruvkun winning the medicine prize. Last year, the chemistry prize was awarded to a trio of scientists.
title: 2024 Nobel prize in Chemistry goes to David Baker, Demis Hassabis & John M. Jumper

description: Lamar Jackson led the Baltimore Ravens to a dramatic 41-38 overtime win over the Bengals, earning Tom Brady's praise for his performance. Jackson completed 26 of 42 passes for 348 yards, four touchdowns, and rushed for 55 yards, highlighting his dual-threat capability.
title: Tom Brady admitted that he could never complete one Lamar Jackson record

description: Mercedes-Benz has unveiled the 2024 E-Class Long Wheelbase in India, with prices ranging from Rs 78.5 lakh to Rs 92.5 lakh. The updated model features design tweaks, advanced MBUX Superscreen infotainment, enhanced rear-seat comfort, and multiple engine options, including a mild hybrid system. It's locally produced in Pune.
title: Mercedes-Benz E-Class LWB launched in India at Rs 78.5 lakh

description: BSP leader Mayawati announced the party's intention to contest assembly elections in Jharkhand, Maharashtra, and Delhi, following their poor performance in Haryana. She attributed the disappointing results to the casteist mentality of the Jat community, despite BSP's alliance with INLD in the polls.
title: BSP will contest assembly elections in J'Khand, Maha and Delhi

description: Acidity can be super uncomfortable, but the good news is that you don’t have to suffer for long! With these simple, natural remedies, you can quickly get rid of the burning sensation and get back to feeling good. If you find that you’re dealing with acidity more often, it might be a good idea to make some lifestyle changes, like cutting back on spicy foods and eating smaller portions.
title: Acidity? Home remedies for quicker relief

description: NASA plans to send humans to Mars by 2035, with a six to seven-month round trip and 500 days on the Martian surface. The Artemis program, which successfully completed Artemis I in 2022, is crucial for preparing astronauts. Artemis III aims to land at the Moon's south pole in 2026, gaining necessary experience for Mars exploration.
title: Nasa’s Artemis program plans to send humans to Mars by 2035 in search for life

description: The trailer for 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' is out, starring Kartik Aaryan, Vidya Balan, and Triptii Dimri. Director Anees Bazmee expressed excitement about pushing the horror-comedy genre's boundaries. The cast and crew presented the trailer at Jaipur's Raj Mandir Cinema. The film, releasing this Diwali, continues the franchise's blend of thrills, chills, and humor.
title: 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' trailer: Kartik, Vidya starrer promises spooky Diwali fest

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has denied reports of shifting India’s matches in the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy to the UAE due to political tensions. PCB asserted all matches, including the final, will be hosted in Pakistan, despite ongoing concerns. ICC has not announced any venue changes, but a hybrid model, as seen in the 2023 Asia Cup, is speculated.
title: CT final to be moved from Lahore? PCB break silence on report

description: Former England captain Joe Root broke Sunil Gavaskar's record of 34 Test centuries during the first Test against England in Multan. Root, known for his versatility against both spin and pace, reached his 35th Test hundred, surpassing cricket legends Mahela Jayawardene, Brian Lara, and Younis Khan.
title: Joe Root hits 35th Test hundred, breaks Sunil Gavaskar's record

description: India's IT sector is set to see a 20-25% increase in campus hiring this fiscal year, driven by demand for AI, cybersecurity, cloud computing, and data analytics. Leading firms like TCS, Infosys, and Wipro are spearheading the recruitment efforts, focusing on fresh talent to address skill gaps.
title: Hiring at engineering colleges to jump 25%: TCS & these IT cos to lead

description: Rahul Gandhi thanked Jammu and Kashmir residents for their support, viewing India's victory there as a win for democracy and constitutional values. Despite losses in Haryana, he emphasized the Congress's dedication to social and economic justice. The BJP attained 48 seats in Haryana, whereas the INDIA bloc secured 49 out of 90 seats in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: ‘Analysing unexpected results’: Rahul’s first reaction after poll debacle

description: A college student named Sundar from Presidency College died from injuries after a clash with Pachaiyappa's College students at Chennai Central railway station. The attack was linked to a 'route-thala' issue. Periamet police have arrested six students from Pachaiyappa's College and altered the case to murder. Sundar succumbed to his injuries at Rajiv Gandhi Govt General Hospital.
title: Chennai college student killed in group clash, 6 held

description: Malayalam actor TP Madhavan passed away on October 9, leaving behind a legacy of memorable roles in movies like ‘Kalyana Raman’ and ‘Pulival Kalyanam’. His last rites will be held on October 10 at Santhi Kavadam. Madhavan, who had been on a ventilator due to stomach ailments, also served as the first General Secretary of AMMA. He acted in over 60 films and TV serials before taking a break due to Amnesia. He spent his final years at Gandhi Bhavan, where he received prestigious awards.
title: Malayalam actor TP Madhavan passes away at 88

description: Omar Abdullah, buoyed by National Conference's victory in Jammu-Kashmir elections, urges the Centre to restore full statehood to the Union Territory. He highlights that J&K was promised statehood before 2019, unlike Delhi. Emphasizing coordination with the central government, he notes that proper relations will benefit J&K's progress and relief in key issues.
title: Rivalry with BJP, not with Centre: Omar Abdullah after J&K poll win

description: The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) has decided to contest the upcoming Delhi assembly elections independently, ruling out an alliance with the Congress. AAP spokesperson Priyanka Kakkar stated that the party aims to highlight its achievements over the past decade while contrasting itself against what she termed as the 'overconfident Congress' and 'arrogant BJP.'
title: After Haryana results, AAP says no alliance with Cong for Delhi polls

description: Margaret Court leads with 64 Grand Slam titles, followed by Martina Navratilova with 59. Serena Williams and Billie Jean King each have 39 titles, while Roy Emerson totals 28. These tennis legends' achievements across singles, doubles, and mixed doubles highlight their versatility and dominance.
title: Top 5 legends with most Grand Slam titles in tennis history

description: Queensland captain Marnus Labuschagne baffled fans and commentators during a Sheffield Shield match by positioning a fielder directly behind the umpire. This unconventional tactic proved effective as Labuschagne took 2 wickets for 5 runs in 6.2 overs. Western Australia scored 465 runs led by centuries from Josh Inglis and Sam Whiteman.
title: Watch: Marnus Labuschagne's 'wild' field placement stuns everyone

description: RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das emphasised India's economic stability and strength, highlighting declining inflation and robust growth. He noted rising foreign exchange reserves, fiscal consolidation, and a resilient financial sector. The repo rate remains at 6.5%, with real GDP growth projected at 7.2% for 2024-25. Focus remains on inflation control and promoting growth.
title: RBI chief Shaktikanta Das's big confidence in India’s growth story

description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg and his wife Priscilla Chan attended the nuptials of Facebook employees Aditya Agarwal and Ruchi Sanghvi in Goa, 2020.
title: Anant Ambani's wedding was not the first marriage that FB founder attended in India

description: Former Union minister Rajeev Chandrasekhar shared an old video of Prime Minister Modi consoling Vinesh Phogat after her Tokyo Olympics loss, highlighting PM Modi's empathy. Despite Phogat's win in Julana assembly seat, Congress lost to BJP in Haryana, with BJP securing an absolute majority in the 90-member assembly.
title: 'Don’t let success ...': PM Modi's advise to Vinesh Phogat in old video

description: Hyundai Motor India’s IPO will be open from October 15-17, marking the largest public issue in India's history. Set at Rs 1,865-1,960 per share, the IPO aims to raise up to Rs 27,856 crore.
title: Hyundai IPO, India’s largest, set to open next week: Top 10 things to know

description: MI5's Director General Ken McCallum highlighted growing threats from Russia's GRU, Iran, and terrorist groups like al Qaeda and Islamic State. Investigations into state threats have surged by 48% over the past year. Since 2017, MI5 and British police have disrupted 43 late-stage plots, with a concerning increase in youth involvement in terrorism-related activities.
title: Russia on mission 'to generate mayhem on European streets,' says UK's Security Service

description: India's Women's T20 World Cup campaign faces a crucial turning point after one win and one loss. They must win against Sri Lanka and Australia convincingly to keep semi-final hopes alive. Ahead of the two pivotal matches, TimesofIndia.com spoke to former India player Reema Malhotra on the campaign so far and way forward.
title: Exclusive: 'Lack of intent from India in T20 WC a cause of concern'

description: Shiv Sena's Saamana editorial criticizes Congress's overconfidence and internal conflicts as reasons for their loss in Haryana elections. It suggests Congress mismanaged a favorable anti-BJP sentiment. Other INDIA bloc partners, including AAP and CPI, also question Congress's approach and advocate for seat sharing in elections to avoid similar outcomes.
title: 'Art of turning victory into defeat ... ': Shiv Sena on Congress's Haryana debacle

description: BJP's delight in the Haryana poll results saw its members indulging in sweets, mocking Rahul Gandhi's jalebi reference during campaigns. Achieving a third consecutive victory, the party relished the irony against pre-poll predictions. Social media buzzed with 'Jalebi Ready Hai?' and similar trends, in a lively shift of celebrations from Congress to BJP.
title: 'Jalebi teri, Haryana mera': 'Sweet' turn of events in election results

description: In Haryana, AAP faced a significant defeat, failing to win any seats and capturing less than 2% of the vote share despite a strong campaign led by Arvind Kejriwal. Conversely, AAP celebrated a victory in Jammu and Kashmir, winning the Doda constituency and marking its legislative presence in five states.
title: Despite Kejriwal’s emotive appeals, AAP fails to open acc in Haryana

description: The US Department of Justice is considering breaking up Google's business segments as a remedy in its antitrust case, following a ruling that declared Google holds an illegal monopoly in the search market.
title: US may be planning to break-up Google, gets this Dec deadline

description: Arshdeep Singh, India's left-arm pacer, is set to potentially become the nation's second-highest T20I wicket-taker during the ongoing series against Bangladesh. With 86 wickets, he needs just four more to surpass Jasprit Bumrah and Bhuvneshwar Kumar. India’s next two matches are critical for Arshdeep's milestone achievement.
title: Arshdeep on the brink of breaking Bumrah, Bhuvneshwar records

description: RBI governor Shaktikanta Das announced enhancements to UPI transaction limits, boosting the per transaction limit for UPI 123Pay and increasing the UPI Lite wallet limit.
title: New UPI transaction limits announced! Check here

description: A spirited Indian team gears up to face Bangladesh in the second T20I in Delhi after a dominant seven-wicket win in Gwalior. With India unlikely to change their winning lineup, key players like Arshdeep Singh and Hardik Pandya, who took a practice day off, are expected to clinch the series with another solid performance.
title: India's playing XI vs B'desh: Will they stick to the winning combination?

description: Geoffrey Hinton and John J. Hopfield have received the Nobel Prize in Physics for pioneering work on artificial neural networks. Their research laid the groundwork for current AI systems like ChatGPT. Hinton also warned about potential risks of AI, emphasizing the need for safety research to keep AI under human control.
title: 'Godfather of AI' gets Nobel Prize in Physics; shares his big AI worry

description: In Jammu and Kashmir's Anantnag district, security forces have recovered the bullet-riddled body of missing Territorial Army soldier Hilal Ahmad Bhat from the Sanglan forest area. Bhat was allegedly abducted, and his disappearance prompted extensive search operations. Meanwhile, a recent anti-terrorist operation in Kupwara saw the neutralization of two terrorists.
title: J&K: Body of jawan abducted by terrorists found with 'gunshot wounds'

description: Dussehra festival, falling on October 12, 2024, symbolizes the victory of good over evil, celebrated with great enthusiasm across India. It honors Lord Rama's triumph over Ravana and Goddess Durga's victory over Mahishasura. This day marked by various rituals and the burning of effigies holds significant religious, cultural, and historical importance among Hindus.
title: Dussehra 2024: When is Vijayadashami? Know date and significance

description: Afspa has been extended for another six months in Tinsukia, Dibrugarh, Charaideo, and Sivasagar districts of Assam, citing potential security threats from disturbances in Bangladesh. Authorities highlight improvements in Assam's security but express concerns over internal law and order. The controversial act, opposed by human rights groups, grants wide-ranging powers to security forces.
title: Afspa extended in 4 Assam districts amid 'disturbances' in Bangladesh

description: The International Space Station captured a view of Hurricane Milton, which re-intensified into a Category 5 storm, heading towards Florida. NOAA researchers are collecting data to improve forecasts, with the storm expected to hit the Tampa Bay area by October 9 or 10. Satellites reveal the hurricane’s extreme convection currents and small, powerful eye.
title: Stunning visuals from space shows Hurricane Milton swirling over Earth

description: Rohit Sharma, India's Test and ODI captain, was spotted in Mumbai interacting warmly with fans while on a break. He delighted a fan by wishing her a happy birthday. Rohit, along with Virat Kohli and Ravindra Jadeja, retired from T20Is after India's T20 World Cup win. His approachable nature continues to captivate fans.
title: Rohit Sharma delights fan with 'birthday wish' on Mumbai street - Watch

description: NOAA has released video footage of a Lockheed WP-3D Orion aircraft encountering severe turbulence while flying into Hurricane Milton. The mission aimed to gather critical data for hurricane research. The footage shows intense rainfall and violent shaking, highlighting the challenges faced by researchers collecting key storm metrics.
title: Terrifying video shows plane flying through Hurricane Milton

description: Melania Trump's memoir 'Melania' reveals her first meeting with Donald Trump at a 1998 Fashion Week party, where he was with another woman but focused on Melania. She declined to give her number but took his instead. Later, they dated and married in 2005. Melania supports women's reproductive rights, differing from Donald's views on abortion.
title: 'Accompanied by blonde woman': Melania recalls her 1st meeting with Trump

description: In Anantnag, Jammu and Kashmir, two Territorial Army soldiers were abducted by terrorists in a forest area. One of the soldiers managed to escape. Security forces have launched a search operation to locate and rescue the remaining soldier, as reported by ANI sources.
title: Two soldiers abducted by terrorists in J&K's Anantnag, rescue efforts on

description: The RG Kar rape-murder trial involving Sanjay Roy, accused of the Aug 9 crime against a junior doctor, starts Nov 4. The CBI charge sheet details evidence including DNA matches, forensic findings, and injury analysis. Roy, who maintains his innocence, awaits trial where he will be represented by his lawyer.
title: Kolkata rape-murder: CBI chargesheet reveals disturbing details

description: Hardik Pandya's all-round performance helped India secure a T20I win against Bangladesh in Gwalior. Despite Pandya's unbeaten 39 off 16 balls and effective bowling, former cricketer RP Singh cautioned against overestimating his form due to Bangladesh's poor play. Singh praised Pandya’s improved fitness and full four-over spells but emphasized stronger opposition as a true test.
title: 'Performance vs B'desh shouldn't get us excited': RP on Hardik's form

description: The Indian women's cricket team faces Sri Lanka in the T20 World Cup with Harmanpreet Kaur fit to play. Despite a win over Pakistan, their performance has been inconsistent, particularly in batting. Key player Smriti Mandhana must lead against Sri Lanka’s spin-heavy attack to improve their net run rate and stay in contention.
title: Women's T20 World Cup: Do Indian batters have a higher gear?

description: Israel marked the anniversary of the deadly October 7 attack by Hamas, which left over 1,200 dead and saw 251 hostages taken. The assault, striking during the Jewish holiday of Simchat Torah, involved rockets and militant breaches of the Gaza-Israel border. Israel's military responded with extensive airstrikes, and Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu declared a decisive, prolonged retaliation.
title: Israel shares disturbing video of chaos during Oct 7 Hamas onslaught

description: Captain Suryakumar Yadav, leading a rejuvenated Team India, is set to wrap up the T20 series against Bangladesh. His dedication and strategic conversations with players signify his commitment to evolving the team, with a focus on preparing for the 2026 T20 World Cup. The involvement of coach Gambhir and chief selector Agarkar emphasizes the plan to build a T20-specific squad.
title: 2nd T20I: India face Bangladesh with eye on 2026 T20 World Cup

description: French authorities expelled Omar bin Laden, son of the late Osama bin Laden, due to social media posts advocating terrorism. Interior Minister Bruno Retailleau confirmed the legality of this national security measure, including a ban preventing Omar from re-entering France for any reason.
title: 'Apology for terrorism': Osama bin Laden's son ordered to leave France

description: Australia's dominating 60-run win over New Zealand in the ICC Women's T20 World Cup puts them atop Group A, complicating India's route to the semifinals. India must win their next two matches convincingly to improve their net run rate and secure a top-two spot. New Zealand and Pakistan remain strong contenders in the race.
title: Women's T20 World Cup: How India can qualify for the semifinals

description: Kane Williamson will miss the start of New Zealand's Test series against India due to a groin strain. Mark Chapman has been called as his replacement. Williamson is expected to return later in the tour. Michael Bracewell will play the first Test before being replaced by Ish Sodhi. The series starts in Bengaluru on October 16.
title: Big blow for NZ! Williamson set to miss start of Test series vs India

description: In response to complaints about inadequate respect from officials, the UP parliamentary affairs department directed senior bureaucrats to offer MLAs chairs equal to theirs. This mandate includes providing a similar chair or sofa and instructs officials to save MLAs' phone numbers and ensure timely communication.
title: Offer chair as per MLAs’ status, UP order tells official

description: PDP is left with only three assembly seats in post-370 J&K, posing an existential threat to the party as no members of the Mufti family are present. Despite this, PDP aims to reconnect with the masses and challenge the government, while BJP remains confined to Jammu.
title: No Mufti in house, yet PDP may live to fight another day

description: Aam Aadmi Party, expanding its beyond Delhi and Punjab, gained a significant milestone in Jammu and Kashmir by winning the Doda assembly constituency with candidate Mehraj Malik. AAP now has representation in five states, demonstrating its growing influence in Indian politics.
title: AAP scores a surprise, finds foothold in J&K

description: SpiceJet, after securing Rs 3,000 crore in funding, plans to restore all its grounded planes within 18-24 months, allocating Rs 400 crore for spares and maintenance. Meanwhile, it will wet-lease aircraft to enhance capacity, aiming for a 100-aircraft fleet by the end of 2026.
title: Grounded planes to fly again in 2 years: SpiceJet

description: GlaxoSmithKline Pharma, celebrating 100 years in India, is shifting to a specialty-focused model by entering the oncology market and expanding its preventive healthcare through adult vaccines. With 30 crore prescriptions annually, GSK aims to innovate and grow its portfolio, highlighting price strategies catering to a broad market range, from general medicines to high-value therapies.
title: GlaxoSmithKline Pharma to enter oncology market, launch adult vax

description: Cognizant faces legal trouble after a US jury found it guilty of discriminating against non-Indian job applicants. The class action lawsuit, representing around 2,000 former employees, claimed Cognizant replaced American workers with South Asian, visa-ready individuals from India. The company plans to appeal against the verdict.
title: Cognizant biased against non-Indians: US court

description: The NC-Congress alliance's recent victory is seen as a rejection of BJP's policies and misuse of constitutional power, according to Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge. Congratulating NC leaders, Kharge emphasized the restoration of J&K's statehood as a top priority. The coalition government aims to meet people's aspirations with a transparent, accountable administration.
title: J&K statehood restoration will be top priority, says Congress

description: The J&K LG will have powers similar to the Delhi LG, overseeing key areas including police and prisons. Amendments enhance his control over critical appointments and law enforcement strategies. This might lead to tensions with the elected J&K government, but both parties may need to adapt to these new dynamics in governance.
title: J&K headed for winter of discontent? It will depend on Lt Guv’s playbook

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman stressed the importance of examining facts before criticizing Sebi chief Madhabi Puri Buch following allegations by Hindenburg Research. She emphasized the transparency brought by Indian regulators and called for a review of consumer and wholesale price indices, while warning against unsustainable freebie giveaways by state governments.
title: Indian regulators have brought greater transparency, says FM

description: Despite a strong nationwide performance, Congress falters in Jammu, securing just one seat and failing to challenge BJP's dominance. National Conference's chief criticized Congress for neglecting Jammu, undermining alliance efforts and allowing BJP to capitalize with 29 seats in the region.
title: Big win for INDIA bloc fails to hide failure of Congress in Jammu

description: Australia secured a commanding 60-run victory over New Zealand in the Women's T20 World Cup, leading Group A with outstanding performances from Alyssa Healy, Beth Mooney, and Megan Schutt. New Zealand's loss affects their net run rate and opens opportunities for India and Pakistan to advance in the tournament standings, pending their upcoming matches.
title: Women's T20 World Cup: How Australia's big win over NZ helps India

description: BJP's dream of forming its first government in J&K remains unfulfilled, despite emerging as the second largest party with 29 seats in the assembly polls post Article 370 nullification. NC-Congress combine gained a clear mandate, while BJP saw a rise in the poll percentage.
title: Quantum of solace for BJP: Defeated but best show yet

description: National Conference's success in J&K's Lok Sabha elections is attributed to the presence of clerics Mian Altaf Ahmad and Aga Ruhullah Mehdi. They significantly affected the campaign, consolidating votes across various Muslim sects and communities, and bringing in strong religious and political support.
title: Faith and politics: NC's double-engine spiritual drive unified Muslim votes

description: The Broadband India Forum (BIF) is staunchly opposing Reliance Jio's call for a revised consultation paper on satellite communication spectrum rules. BIF argues that the current approach is aligned with the Telecommunications Act 2023, which mandates administrative allocation of spectrum. Reliance Jio contends that the existing paper doesn't ensure fair competition between satellite and terrestrial services.
title: Jio's Satcom demand against the law passed by the Parliament, claims BIF

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 9, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope today: Read your today's astrological predictions
